<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-05T12:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-05T12:40:00-05:00" n="1116" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1116">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4134.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nuevo
                                    Laredo</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-05T11:00:00-06:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Huerta has arrested Villa and sent him to Mexico City for trial. Family
                            of Orozco en route to Europe, he to follow, it is believed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>